 Prospects |accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width =\"700\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Name''' \n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Position'''\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Games'''\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Goals'''\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Assists'''\n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''Pts''' \n! style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}};\" | '''[[Penalty (ice hockey)|{{color|#FFFFFF|PIM}}]]'''\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| {{sortname|Gary|Delonge|nolink=1}} || [[Centre (ice hockey)|C]] ||- ||39 ||35 ||'''74''' ||-\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"f0f0f0\"\n| {{sortname|Pete|Shipman|nolink=1}} || [[Forward (ice hockey)|F]] ||- ||26 ||45 ||'''71''' ||-\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| {{sortname|John|Malloy|nolink=1}} || [[Centre (ice hockey)|C]] ||37 ||16 ||52 ||'''68''' ||-\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"f0f0f0\"\n| {{sortname|Bill|Bok|nolink=1}} || [[Forward (ice hockey)|F]] ||- ||32 ||34 ||'''66''' ||-\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| {{sortname|Vern|Sketchley|nolink=1}} || [[Winger (ice hockey)|W]] ||- ||- ||- ||- ||73\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"f0f0f0\"\n| {{sortname|Paul|Kinney|nolink=1}} || [[Winger (ice hockey)|W]] ||- ||- ||- ||- ||88\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| {{sortname|Dudley|Fitzpatrick|nolink=1}} || [[Defenseman|D]] ||- ||- ||- ||- ||88\n|}\n\n==Players drafted into the NHL==\n===[[1979 NHL Entry Draft]]<ref name = guide>{{cite news|title=Miami men's Hockey 2018-19 Record Book|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/miamiredhawks.com/documents/2018/9/11/2018_19_Hockey_Record_Book.pdf |publisher=Miami RedHawks |accessdate=February 13, 2019}}</ref>===\nMiami did not have any players selected in the NHL Entry Draft.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|50em}}\n\n{{NCAA Division I Men's Ice Hockey Champion navbox}}\n{{Miami RedHawks men's ice hockey navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1978-79 Miami Redskins men's ice hockey season}}\n[[Category:Miami RedHawks men's ice hockey seasons]]\n[[Category:1978 in sports]]\n[[Category:1979 in sports]]\n[[Category:1978\u201379 in American ice hockey by team|Miami]]\n[[Category:1978\u201379 NCAA Division I men's ice hockey by team|Miami]]\n[[Category:1978 in sports in Ohio|Miami Redskins ice hockey]]\n[[Category:1979 in sports in Ohio|Miami Redskins ice hockey]]\n", "text_old": "{{NCAAIceHockeyTeamSeason\n  |Image              = \n  |ImageSize          = \n  |Season             = [[1978\u201379 NCAA Division I men's ice hockey season|1978\u201379]]\n  |Team               = Miami Redskins\n  |Sex                = men\n  |Conference         = Mid\u2013Central Collegiate Hockey Association\n  |ShortConference    = MCCHA\n  |ConferenceRank     = 2nd\n  |Poll#1             = \n  |Poll#1Rank         = \n  |Poll#2             = \n  |Poll#2Rank         =  \n  |Record             = 22\u201314\u20131\n  |ConfRecord         = 12\u20133\u20131\n  |HomeRecord         = 15\u20134\u20130\n  |RoadRecord         = 7\u201310\u20131\n  |NeutralRecord      = 0\u20130\u20130\n  |HeadCoach          = [[Steve Cady]]\n  |AsstCoaches        = \n  |Captain            = Gary DeLonge<br>Paul Kinney<br>John Mallory\n  |AltCaptain         = \n  |Arena              = [[Goggin Ice Arena|Miami Ice Arena]]\n  |Champion           = Mid\u2013Central Collegiate Hockey Association Tournament, Champion\n  |NCAATourney        = \n  |NCAATourneyResult  = \n|prevseason           = \n|nextseason           = [[1979\u201380 Miami Redskins men's ice hockey season|1979\u201380]]\n  |headerstyle        = {{CollegePrimaryStyle|Miami RedHawks |color=#FFFFFF}}\n  |labelstyle         = background:#eeeeee;\n}}\nThe '''1978\u201379 Miami Redskins men's ice hockey team''' represented the [[Miami University]] in [[college ice hockey]]. In its inaugural varsity season the team was coached by [[Steve Cady]] and played at the newly opened [[Goggin Ice Arena|Miami Ice Arena]].\n\n==Season==\nMiami's ice hockey program was promoted to varsity status in the summer of 1978.<ref name = guide>{{cite news|title=Miami men's Hockey 2018-19 Record Book|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/miamiredhawks.com/documents/2018/9/11/2018_19_Hockey_Record_Book.pdf |publisher=Miami RedHawks |accessdate=February 13, 2019}}</ref> In their first season the Redskins remained in the [[Mid\u2013Central Collegiate Hockey Association]], a small collection of local club teams, mainly so it could field a full schedule. Miami was also able to schedule 10 games against [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] opponents that would take place throughout the season.\n\nAfter an initial win over [[Cincinnati Bearcats|Cincinnati]], Miami was beaten soundly in four consecutive games. The losses were against the top-tier squads which was a trend that would continue throughout the season. Miami finished the regular season with a very good 12\u20133\u20131 record in conference, but lost all 10 games against the D-I teams. Miami's up and down year came to an end with the MCCHA tournament, with the entire championship being played in it's home arena. The Redskins took advantage of the opportunity and routed [[Eastern Michigan Eagles|Eastern Michigan]] before shutting out Michigan\u2013Dearborn to claim the championship.<ref name = results>{{cite news|title=Miami Recensio 1979 |url=https://digital.lib.miamioh.edu/digital/collection/p17240coll2/id/20432 |work=Miami University |accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs Miami continued to transition into a full Division I schedule, the team knew it had a long way to go before it could compete with the rest of the big programs.\n\n==Roster<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eliteprospects.com/team/1248/miami-univ.-ohio/1978-1979?sort=jersey |title=1978-79 Miami Univ. |work=Elite Prospects |accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>==\n\n{{College ice hockey team roster|NHL Team=yes}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=1 |first=Tom |last=Brown |class=jr |rs= |pos=G |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=2 |first=Dudley |last=Fitzpatrick |class=jr |rs= |pos=D |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=3 |first=Ken |last=Johnson |class=sr |rs= |pos=D |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=4 |first=Tom |last=Smith |class=sr |rs= |pos=W |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=5 |first=Dave |last=McClintock |class=fr |rs= |pos=D |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=6 |first=Matt |last=McIntyre |class=sr |rs= |pos=D |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=7 |first=Pete |last=Shipman |class=jr |rs= |pos=F |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=8 |first=Mike |last=VanSchaack |class=so |rs= |pos=W |ft= |in= |wt= |birthyear= |birthmonth= |birthday= |state= |hometown= |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |inj= |cap=}}\n\n{{CIHplayer |num=9 |first=Gary |last=DeLonge |class=sr |rs= |pos=C |ft=6 |in=0 |wt=181 |birthyear=1955 |birthmonth=4 |birthday=14 |state=New Jersey |hometown=[[Summit, New Jersey]] |prevteam= |prevleague= |NHLteam= |NHLpick= |NHLyear= |in